                        Privacy Policy & Terms of Use


   The United States Mint appreciates your visit to our Web site. We
   support your right to know about information we collect and how it will
   be used. Our services are growing and our practices may change, so
   please check back for updates to our Privacy Statement.

   Click here to see our full privacy statement.
     * You do not have to give us any personal information to visit our
       site.
     * We do not attempt to collect personally identifiable information
       from children under age 13.
     * The U.S. Mint does not rent or sell your personal information.
     * We may use personal information provided online to respond to
       electronic inquiries (job applications, product orders and
       inquiries, etc.) and distribute catalogs, job and other offerings,
       newsletters and educational materials, and we and our contractors
       store and use this information to process and verify requests and
       provide our products and services.
     * We use software to maintain security, improve service and collect
       data for statistical purposes.
          + Web statistics can be viewed here
     * We use cookie technology to keep you connected to our server and
       operate our shopping cart. The U.S. Mint does not now use cookies
       to store individually identifiable information or track actions
       over time or across non-U.S. Mint websites.

   Click here to view the complete text of the U.S. Mint's Privacy
   Statement.


